The paper presents a language model for implementing typed multiparty sessions using hypersequents, which is based on classical linear logic. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with choreographies and processes, which are topics related to Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses server invocation and logic-driven compilation, which are topics related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Systems and Control (cs.SC) sub-categories.
